    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/paypal-payment-button-with-sap-build-workzone-amp-s-4hana-public-cloud-via/qaq-p/14084936</id>
    <title>PayPal Payment Button with SAP Build Workzone &amp; S/4HANA Public Cloud via PayPal Braintree</title>
    <updated>2025-04-24T02:56:22.586000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>C_BuildsSAP</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/830553</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P class=""&gt;We’ve developed a custom sales platform using &lt;STRONG&gt;SAP Build Workzone&lt;/STRONG&gt;, integrated with &lt;STRONG&gt;SAP S/4HANA Public Cloud&lt;/STRONG&gt;, and are in the process of implementing &lt;STRONG&gt;PayPal&lt;/STRONG&gt; as a payment method.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;We are currently using &lt;STRONG&gt;PayPal Braintree&lt;/STRONG&gt; as our payment service provider (PSP), and the integration requires the use of the PayPal &lt;STRONG&gt;JavaScript SDK&lt;/STRONG&gt; – &lt;A class="" href="https://developer.paypal.com/sdk/js/" target="_new" rel="noopener nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://developer.paypal.com/sdk/js/&lt;/A&gt; – to render the PayPal payment button on the front end.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;We’re encountering issues embedding/loading this PayPal JavaScript SDK within the Workzone environment. Anyone know of a workaround or how to load a JavaScript library on SAP Build?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;The ultimate goal is: the user should be able to see the PayPal payment button on Checkout screen, and on click, it should trigger a new page to sign into their PayPal account and load the checkout details i.e. total price and allow them to choose and submit payment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/paypal-payment-button-with-sap-build-workzone-amp-s-4hana-public-cloud-via/qaq-p/14084936"/>
    <published>2025-04-24T02:56:22.586000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
